==Description==

"Sewing Rebellion was started by textile worker and activist Frau Fiber, under the gospel “stop shopping, start sewing,” with the purpose of encouraging others to learn how to sew and thus be able to create unique and personal clothing. Working with accessible materials, sewing rebellion members are also known for the creativity with which they redesign and repurpose old clothes, fabrics and such."
(http://openmaterials.org/2009/11/13/sewing-rebellion/)


